Module kivakit.core
Package com.telenav.kivakit.core.object

Class LazyMap<Key,Value>

java.lang.Object
com.telenav.kivakit.core.object.LazyMap<Key,Value>
Type Parameters:
Value - The type of value to create
public class LazyMap<Key,Value> extends Object
A lazy-initializing map.

Given a Mapper that creates values for keys, lazy-creates map entries when get(Key) is called. After that the value is cached in the map and get(Key) will return the same value. clear() can be used to clear the map, and remove(Key) can be used to remove the value for a particular key.

Example

  LazyMap<Identifier, Session> session = MapLazy.of(Session::new);

     [...]

  session.get(identifier);

jonathanl (shibo)
